@node story "Story"

So.... in far far glaxy....

A 'cup of tea' break at my job, author (thats me:-) sitting
infront a linux machine (i386 based ;()... trying to run
a UnusableAmigaEmulator... oki.. one minute....ten....
ahhh, amiga shell... now its time to make a litte cleanup
like commenting stuff downloaded form inet....
@{b}AGGGGRHHH!@{ub} Where is a c:command?
Wanish!? Yes...

Some SetCommand() and PutStr() magic and we haw a outstanding
and kicking @{fg shine}BOUT @{fg text}

@endnode

@node bug "Bug"

Uhhh yes.... i must admit that i found ONE error ;>
Take look on exampel

@{b}bout Ozone-Proklive.exe Rulling demo from Sat'98@{ub}

This shound add a comment Rulling demo from Sat'9 
to Ozone-Proklive.exe file.... yes :>
But it add only a first word "Rulling" why?
My foult ;] try using

@{b}bout Ozone-Proklive.exe "Rulling demo from Sat'98"@{ub}

and now everything should be just fine (at least ya got kick 3.5;-)
@endnode

